==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Antecedence
<hw>An`te*ced"ence</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act or state of going before in time; precedence.</def>
<rj><au>H. Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>An apparent motion of a planet
toward the west; retrogradation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Antecedency</ent>⟦br⟧
